.\" kerberos-vscode manual page
.TH KERBEROS-VSCODE 1 "March 2026" "kerberos-vscode 1.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
 kerberos-vscode \- acquire a Kerberos TGT into an isolated cache and launch Visual Studio Code
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B kerberos-vscode
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBkerberos-vscode\fR acquires a Kerberos Ticket Granting Ticket (TGT) for the \fBkerberos.ORG\fR realm into a file-based cache and then launches Visual Studio Code so that extensions (for example, MSSQL using Windows/Integrated authentication) can use that cache via \fBKRB5CCNAME\fR.

The tool may update \fI/etc/krb5.conf\fR to ensure the configured realm and KDC list match the organization configuration.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 2
User chose to quit after KDC connectivity prompt.
.TP
.B 3
No valid TGT found in the selected cache.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /usr/local/bin/kerberos-vscode
Installed CLI tool.
.TP
.I /etc/krb5.conf
Kerberos configuration file (may be modified).
.TP
.I /tmp/krb5cc_vscode
Kerberos credential cache.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR kinit (1),
.BR klist (1),
.BR krb5.conf (5)
